IT IS SENIOR NIGHT for the NLL Champs!

Join us tonight on the Jacket Sports Network as we bring you the final regular season game of 2020. Your Jackets take on the Generals of Anthony Wayne. The first meeting was a good game in the first half until the jackets dominated the 3rd quarter. I am sure the Generals will be looking for a little payback. We will have interviews with coaches and players, and as always a special guest or two.

Please join us live beginning around 7:00pm for the Savage and Associates pre-game show on the Jacket Sports Network live on Facebook. If we have a good connection we will try to provide video as well... especially of the pregame ceremony for the seniors. Lets Go Jackets!!!

post_text:
Rise up!!! Make NO mistake, you are in Jacket country.

IT IS GAME TIME!!!
Time to battle for the BELL!!

Please join us tonight and support the cheerleaders, band, and football team as we head across the river to play the mother of all rivalry games - Maumee vs Perrysburg. #TheBellStays

Now if for some reason you cannot be there in person, please hit us up on the Jacket Sports Network.

Wow!!! Went to my first Cross Country meet this morning to see the Yellow Jackets run. I was blown away! I had no idea! This event was awesome!

First of all it was much bigger than I had imagined. Girl and Boy runners from at least 25 schools I would guess. The girls ran first followed by the boys. Congratulations to the Perrysburg Coaches (Monheim and Madaras) as both races had a Yellow Jacket crossing the line first.

But that wasn‚Äôt the best part; the crowds are amazing. The support from parents, grand-parents, teammates, neighbors, was incredible. And to be honest they weren‚Äôt just cheering for their favorites; Nope, following the finish of the first 30 runners the ‚Äúfeel‚Äù of the race‚Ä¶

post_text:
The Jacket Sports Network Welcomes A New Member to the broadcast team.

It is my pleasure to announce that KYLE ROSS - Perrysburg Freshman (are we calling them 1st Years yet) is joining the Jacket Sports Network. Kyle competes as a golfer on the JV team, and enjoys basketball and baseball. When asked what he wants to do with his life, "sports commentary." PERFECT!!!
